  "name": "Lantern of Empty Light: Mystic Enthrallment",
  "type": "action",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">2</span> Interact (emotion, visual)</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You direct the lantern's light upon a single living creature within 60 feet. That creature must attempt a @Check[type:will|dc:20|traits:emotion,visual] save to resist the light's effects.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected and realizes that you attempted to mentally influence them with the light.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature is unaffected but thinks the light was harmless, unless it knows the true nature of the lantern already.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.AdPVz7rbaVSRxHFg]{Fascinated} by the lantern's light, and remains fascinated as long as you Sustain the Activation, up to 10 minutes.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but you can Sustain the Activation for up to 1 hour. When the effect ends, the fascinated creature remembers any events that took place while fascinated only as indistinct, dream-like memories.</p>"
    },
